Terms of Usage:

The following catalog of stellar parameters is the property of its authors listed above. The data in the catalog may be used freely for all scientific purposes; however, upon usage, please acknowledge the use of the catalog with the following citation: Takeda, G., Ford, E.B., Sills, A., Rasio, F.A., Fischer, D.A., & Valenti, J.A., 2007, ApJS, 168, 297.


Catalog Description:

- Best-estimate parameters are computed from the median values of the derived probability distribution functions (PDFs).
- The mass upper bound is left blank if the tail of the stellar-mass PDF is truncated at 2Msol.
- The median mass is left blank if the tail of the stellar-mass PDF is truncated at 2 Msol and P(2Msol) > 0.2 (Pmax = 1).
- If the mode mass is larger than 2Msol, neither the median mass nor the credible interval is listed in the table. These stars are denoted with an asterisk (*) beside the stellar ID, indicating that the derived stellar parameters may not be reliable due to the possibly insufficient number of stellar evolutionary tracks used for the stellar parameter calculations.

M: Best-estimate stellar mass
Mlow: Lower bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar mass
Mhigh: Upper bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar mass
age: Best-estimate stellar age
agelow: Lower bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar age
agehigh: Upper bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar age
R: Best-estimate stellar radius
Rlow: Lower bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar radius
Rhigh: Upper bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar radius
Mce: Best-estimate stellar convective zone mass
Mce,low: Lower bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar convective zone mass
Mce,high: Upper bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar convective zone mass
Rce: Best-estimate stellar convective zone depth, measured from the stellar surface
Rce,low: Lower bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar convective zone depth
Rce,high: Upper bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated stellar convective zone depth
log(g): Best-estimate surface gravity
log(g)low: Lower bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated surface gravity
log(g)high: Upper bound of the 95.4% credible interval for the estimated surface gravity
